  "body": "I get a prompt:\r\n\r\n\"Gas estimation errored with the following message (see below). The transaction execution will likely fail. Do you want to force sending?\r\nError happened while trying to execute a function inside a smart contract\"\r\n\r\nthe only problem is the lack of following message. \r\n\r\n\r\nDoesnt matter if it is a message in require statement, or custom error (error statement).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\ntype of connection: injected provider\r\n\r\nnetwork: bsc mainnet (56), forked bsc (31337).\r\n\r\n\r\nto pre-empt the question this setup has worked through many consequent updates of remix version up until yesterday (0.37), when problems with \"transaction being reverted by the EVM\" started popping up on certain number of networks (bsc was one of the affected). \r\n\r\nNow  transactions make it to the EVM (thanks for quick fix), but the lack of possibility to see the error message (thus placement), makes working with larger codes nigh impossible.\r\n",
